thomas beaver free library and danville ymca is a historic library and ymca located at danville, montour county, pennsylvania. the two attached buildings were built in 1886. they are  2 1⁄2-story, sandstone buildings with slate roofs in a combined queen anne / second empire style. the buildings feature an octagonal cupola, corbelled stone chimneys, a hipped roof tower, and terra cotta ornament. it was added to the national register of historic places in 1987.